===Etymology===
From {{der|en|enm|happy||fortunate, happy}}, perhaps an alteration of {{der|en|enm|happyn}}, {{m|enm|happen||fortunate, happy}}, possibly related to or from {{der|en|non|heppinn||fortunate, happy}}; and potentially assimilated to be equivalent to {{af|en|hap<t:chance, luck, fortune>|-y<id:adjectival>}}. Compare also {{cog|is|heppinn||lucky}}, {{cog|fo|heppin||fortunate, lucky, happy}}, {{cog|nn|heppen||lucky}}, {{cog|sco|happin||fortunate, blessed}}. See further at {{m|en|hap}}.

